properties.name: Backyard Burger
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer5310 Kingston PikeHome of the best burgers in the whole world! They are so big and juicy and covered with really fresh ingridients. The sides make your meal even better!

properties.name: Carrabba's Italian Grille
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer324 N. Peters Rd This place is the best place for all of the true Italian food lovers. My first time going here was in high school with my family and It is absolutely my favorite place ever. I think the food is so exceptional because the brothers that founded this chain of restaurants visit each location to guarantee that the food still meets the original standards they set. Amazing! Enjoy!

properties.name: Copper Cellar
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer1807 Cumerland AveThe same friend that took me to Wong\'s Palace took me here for my first birthday here. We had so much fun. The food is very savory and bursting with flavor! The thing that Copper Cellar is most famous for is burger night! So you can get full without hurting your wallet! Check it out!

properties.name: Cracker Barrel
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer2920 S. Mall Rd.I ate here for the first time this January on a rest stop for a road trip to Gulf Coast Getaway in Panama City, FL. All I have for this one is one word--catfish!!! Mmmhmm! If this is you, go get \'em!

properties.name: Great American Steakhouse
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer900 Merchant Dr. I first visited this spot with my family when I was 12 yrs old. I was in Knoxville competing in a scholarship Recognition Program. This place is a true classic due to its rich variety.

properties.name: P.F. Chang's China Bistro
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer6741 Kingston PikeFirst went to this swanky establishment last Spring for a friend\'s birthday dinner and girl\'s night out. It is definitely pricy and upscale, but the reward is the wonderful food.

properties.name: Ruby Tuesday's
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer2714 Chapman HwyThe lady I consider my second mother treated me to this pleasant surprise for my Birthday last September. This place has a very well rounded menu to suit all tastes. It is a little pricy, but I promise it is worth it!

properties.name: Soho Cafe
properties.description: Posted by MymanboomerÂ 4433 Kingston PikeIf you are looking for authentic Japanese food, this is the spot for you. I treated to dinner here with a very good friend recently and have been in love ever since. The atmosphere is wonderful, service excellent, and the food? Ooooh...just check it out! I promise you wont be disappointed!

properties.name: Waffle House
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer507 Lovell Rd.Maaaan...this satisfies everything for those late nights after the club was poppin but then hunger is the issue. So many good times with my girls. My personal fave is the Ham and Cheese Omlet with raisin bread toast. So good...and the sevice is always great!

properties.name: Wong's Palace
properties.description: Posted by Mymanboomer4009 Chapman HwyOne of my best guy friends treated me to this restaurant for my birthday last year. In my opinion, this is the best spot for your Chinese fix. The food is always hot and fresh. Plus, service is always with a smile!
